description: The CLIR Recordings at Risk program provides grants for digitizing at-risk audio and audiovisual recordings of significant cultural or scholarly value. It supports institutions working to preserve materials that may otherwise be lost due to media degradation or obsolescence ensuring their long-term accessibility for future research.
